<DOC><DOCNO> AP881221-0253 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-21-88 1718EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f AM-SatellitesContract     12-21 0173</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Satellites Contract,0179</SECOND><HEAD>Martin Marietta Signs Contract To Launch Two Satellites</HEAD><DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Martin Marietta Commercial Titan Inc. on Wednesdayannounced it has signed a contract with Hughes Aircraft Co. tolaunch two communications satellites on Commercial Titan launchvehicles.   Terms of the contract were not announced.   Richard E. Brackeen, president of Commercial Titan, a whollyowned subsidiary of Martin Marietta Corp., said the Hughes contractbrings to six the number of satellites to be launched on theCommercial Titan, according to a Martin Marietta news statement.   Two Hughes HS 601-class communications satellites will belaunched under the contract. The Hughes HS 601 has been selected forthe Navy's next-generation ultra-high-frequency communicationssatellite program. Hughes also will employ the satellites for directbroadcast use during the early 1990s, according to the newsstatement.   The first launch of a Commercial Titan is scheduled for thesummer of 1989 from Cape Canaveral, Fla., when communicationssatellites for the Japan Communication Satellite Co. and the BritishMinistry of Defense will be taken into space.</TEXT></DOC>